[src:image-super-resolution/upsampling] Let *L*/*M* denote the upsampling factor, where *L* > *M*.
[src:image-super-resolution/upsampling] Upsampling requires a lowpass filter after increasing the data rate, and downsampling requires a lowpass filter before decimation.
[src:image-super-resolution/upsampling] Therefore, both operations can be accomplished by a single filter with the lower of the two cutoff frequencies.
